      "date": "2023-12-01 11:38:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIs it reported with host down? if yes - should connection to be down also ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e3550aaabd234e2388814eaf3d308b836b3af44e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 824,
        "name": "Serguei Smirnov",
        "email": "ssmirnov@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "ssmirnov"
      },
      "date": "2023-12-07 18:31:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Is it reported with host down? if yes - should connection to be\n > down also ?\n\nSorry, missed your question. I don't know for sure if it was reported with peer host down, perhaps Shuichi Ihara can confirm. My understanding was that the peer host wasn't actually down, but the local link went down. It is true that we could query link status and ignore the event if the link is down, but I was concerned about race conditions involved, so decided it was easier to just ignore the event and let the connection close because of the tx timeout later on.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
